  Day6Dialog:
  - "Beyond the outer tents, the ground is torn up. Wild plants have been pulled
    out by the roots, and broken baskets lie nearby. Whatever could be eaten here
    has already been taken. Foraging parties have been working this area hard\u2014and
    recently."
  Day7FirstTimeDialog:
  - "At a well near the camp\u2019s edge, you notice extra guards posted. Buckets
    sit unused beside the rim. Someone has tied cloth over the opening to keep debris
    out. The water is still there, but no one is eager to draw from it."
  Day7MetBeforeDialog:
  - "At a well near the camp\u2019s edge, you notice extra guards posted. Buckets
    sit unused beside the rim. Someone has tied cloth over the opening to keep debris
    out. The water is still there, but no one is eager to draw from it."
  Day8FirstTimeDialog:
  - "A cooking fire has burned low without being properly put out. A pot lies on
    its side, its contents spilled into the dirt. The food smells wrong\u2014sour,
    untouched. Someone chose not to eat, or was ordered not to."
  Day8MetBeforeDialog:
  - "A cooking fire has burned low without being properly put out. A pot lies on
    its side, its contents spilled into the dirt. The food smells wrong\u2014sour,
    untouched. Someone chose not to eat, or was ordered not to."
  Day9FirstTimeDialog:
  - Tracks lead away from a familiar path toward a longer route inland. Carts have
    passed through recently, their wheels cutting deep into the soil. The shorter
    route has been avoided. Something ahead was considered unsafe.
  Day9MetBeforeDialog:
  - Tracks lead away from a familiar path toward a longer route inland. Carts have
    passed through recently, their wheels cutting deep into the soil. The shorter
    route has been avoided. Something ahead was considered unsafe.
  Day10FirstTimeDialog:
  - "Today you find a cracked water skin emptied onto the ground. The leather is
    intact\u2014it wasn\u2019t damaged. Someone chose to waste what little water
    they had rather than drink it. The camp still functions, but trust in its supplies
    is thinning."
  Day10MetBeforeDialog:
  - "Today you find a cracked water skin emptied onto the ground. The leather is
    intact\u2014it wasn\u2019t damaged. Someone chose to waste what little water
    they had rather than drink it. The camp still functions, but trust in its supplies
    is thinning."
